Class DummySyncData

java.lang.Object
  edu.byu.ece.rapidSmith.bitstreamTools.bitstream.ConfigurationData
      edu.byu.ece.rapidSmith.bitstreamTools.bitstream.DummySyncData

public class DummySyncData
extends ConfigurationData

Represents the dummy sync data found in Xilinx bitstreams. This object contains a List member that holds all of the sync data. This class contains two prebuilt static DummySyncData objects for V5 and V6. TODO: Create separate classes for V4 sync data vs. v5/v6 sync data

findDummySyncData

public static DummySyncData findDummySyncData(java.util.List<java.lang.Byte> data,
                                              int startIndex)
Find the dummy/sync data in the bitstream starting at the given index and return it as a DummySyncData object. If no sync word (0xaa995566) is found, null is returned. The startIndex is assumed to be the beginning of the dummy data and the dummy/sync data ends after the sync word is found.

Parameters:
data - The data to search through.
startIndex - The starting index in the data given.
Returns:
The dummy sync data if found or null otherwise.
